        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "T3vmB",
          "name": "readerBody",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "height": "fill_container",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 20,
          "padding": 24,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "qco4H",
              "name": "chTitle",
              "fill": "$text-primary",
              "content": "Chapter 7: The Hard Problem",
              "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
              "fontSize": 22,
              "fontWeight": "700"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "QcXmP",
              "name": "para1",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The hard problem of consciousness is the problem of explaining why and how sentient organisms have phenomenal experiences — how and why it is that some internal states are felt states, such as heat or pain, rather than unfelt states.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "sIDZX",
              "name": "para2",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "David Chalmers first articulated the hard problem in 1995, distinguishing it from what he called the 'easy problems' of consciousness, such as explaining the ability to discriminate, categorize, and react to environmental stimuli.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "d3fv8",
              "name": "para3",
              "fill": "$text-secondary",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The question of why these physical processes are accompanied by experience is left unanswered by standard functional explanations. This is the fundamental puzzle that researchers in consciousness studies continue to grapple with today.",
              "lineHeight": 1.6,
              "fontFamily": "Inter",
              "fontSize": 15,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "gEKnH",
          "name": "btmBar3",
          "width": "fill_container",
